    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2021.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 18, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch of the 6th of July, No. 1402. I thank you for the interesting account
                    you have given me of the demonstrations of official and popular feeling produced
                    by the; late tragical events in Mexico.</p>
                <p>You will easily infer the present attitude of this government towards Mexico from
                    a memorandum<note n="*" xml:id="d108fn1">For enclosure see instructions to
                        United States minister to Mexico.</note> made at this department on the 12th
                    instant, in regard to the adventures of Señor Santa Anna at Vera Cruz and Sisal,
                    a copy of which memorandum is herewith transmitted for your information.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
